    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="638"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d638">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.51/438.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Blanchard</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 2, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your November 29, 10 p.m. The Department still believes that the negotiation of
                    temporary loan for $1,500,000 should await the arrival of Haitian
                    commission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
